ENTRY            D6506   20260203   20260508   20260508       D151
SUBENT        D6506001   20260203   20260508   20260508       D151
BIB                 10         31
TITLE      A study on the effect of neutron excess on compound
            and non-compound nuclear reaction cross sections at
            above barrier energies
AUTHOR     (R.K.Sahoo, D.Singh, A.Mahato, P.K.Giri,
            N.Sharma, L.Chhura, R.Mahato, S.B.Linda, H.Kumar,
            S.A.Tali, R.Ali, M.A.Ansari, R.Kumar, S.Muralithar,
            R.P.Singh)
INSTITUTE  (3INDMUA,3INDNSD)
           (3INDIND) Central University of Jharkhand, Ranchi
           (3INDIND) G.F. College, Shahjahanpur, Uttar Pradesh
           (3INDIND) Dr. Shyama Prasad Mukherjee University,
            Ranchi
           (3INDIND) UGC-DAE Consortium for Scientific Research,
            Kolkata Center, Kolkata
           (3INDIND) Nims University Rajasthan, Jaipur
REFERENCE  (J,EPJ/A,61,121,2025)
FACILITY   (VDGT,3INDNSD) 15 UD Pelletron accelerator
SAMPLE     (62-SM-154,ENR=0.987) Isotopically enriched 154Sm
            targets were prepared by vacuum evaporation technique.
            A stack of seven targets (~400-600 ug/cm2 thick) was
            backed with aluminum catcher foils (~1.0-3.0 mg/cm2).
DETECTOR   (HPGE) The detector was pre-calibrated using
            152Er (13.6 years) and 133Ba (10.51 years) sources of
            known activity, with an energy resolution of 2.5 keV
            at 1408 keV.
METHOD     (ACTIV,STTA) irradiated for ~9 hrs.
           (BCINT) The beam current was ~5-7 nA (~1 pnA), as
            measured by an electron-suppressed Faraday cup.
ERR-ANALYS (DATA-ERR) The overall uncertainty is estimated to be
            below 17%.
HISTORY    (20260203C) VT
